\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {8}{\ignorespaces Effect of memory factor $\lambda $ on long-run reputation for an always-honest authority ($\delta =0.95$ fixed). High $\lambda $ causes decay to dominate: even perfect behaviour cannot prevent slow reputation erosion. Low $\lambda $ converges fast but makes reputation volatile. The default $\lambda =0.7$ balances stability and responsiveness.}}{31}{figure.caption.33}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:lambda_sensitivity}{{8}{31}{Effect of memory factor $\lambda $ on long-run reputation for an always-honest authority ($\delta =0.95$ fixed). High $\lambda $ causes decay to dominate: even perfect behaviour cannot prevent slow reputation erosion. Low $\lambda $ converges fast but makes reputation volatile. The default $\lambda =0.7$ balances stability and responsiveness}{figure.caption.33}{}}
