\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {9}{\ignorespaces Effect of participation weight $\alpha $ on reputation recovery after a single cheat event (round 1), followed by honest participation. Lower $\alpha $ produces a deeper initial penalty. All trajectories converge to the same long-run equilibrium ($\approx 0.84$) because the honest-participation score is $1.0$ regardless of $\alpha $.}}{32}{figure.caption.34}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:alpha_sensitivity}{{9}{32}{Effect of participation weight $\alpha $ on reputation recovery after a single cheat event (round 1), followed by honest participation. Lower $\alpha $ produces a deeper initial penalty. All trajectories converge to the same long-run equilibrium ($\approx 0.84$) because the honest-participation score is $1.0$ regardless of $\alpha $}{figure.caption.34}{}}
